The paper deals with the problem of topic modeling, which is a subfield of machine learning and natural language processing. The proposed approach involves fitting a mixture model to the co-occurrence data of a corpus, which is a common technique in unsupervised learning and clustering. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing. The paper also involves optimization and numerical methods, which are relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the use of GPUs for acceleration suggests a possible connection to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.AR (Hardware Architecture).
